All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Ammunition
    Ammunition is shot from towers to kill enemies.
    ArmoredEnemy
    Armored enemy is a strong, beefy enemy.
    Base
    This is the Base class that creates the home base of the game.
    BossEnemy
    Boss enemy is the strongest and beefiest enemy.
    Button
    A rectangular button that the user can press
    Circle
    A circle used for shooting radius of towers
    Counter
    A Counter class that allows you to display a numerical value on screen.
    Enemy
    Enemies try to reach the cosmic secrets.
    EnergyBall
    EnergyBall
    FastEnemy
    Fast enemy is the weakest but fastest enemy.
    FlyingEnemy
    Flying enemy is an enemy that flies over the path.
    GameOver
    Ending world, shows the user's final score as well as the high scores
    GridConverter
    A collection of methods allowing for the conversion between grid coordinates (the index "coordinates" of an object in the 2d array, representing which square the object is in) and world coordinates (the coordinates of said object in the world, in pixels)
    InfoWorld
    Shows the info of all the towers
    Instructions
    Instructions of the game, this is essentially an image
    MyWorld
    MyWorld is where the main "action" of the game takes place.
    PathPiece
    A piece of the path, enemies can use this to determine where to go
    QMTextbox
    A container to display one or multiple lines of text.
    Rocket
    AOE projectile - explodes upon impact dealing damage to surounding enemies.
    SmoothMover
    A variation of an actor that maintains a precise location (using doubles for the co-ordinates instead of ints).
    Square
    A square
    StandardEnemy
    Standard enemy is the easiest, simpliest enemy.
    StatBar
    New and Improved Stat Bar (Formerly Health Bar).
    Timer
    A very simply Timer class that functions as a virtual stopwatch.
    Tower
    Towers are placed to defend against enemies.
    TowerFour
    Turret four is an electric turret.
    TowerOne
    Tower one is the simple turret.
    TowerThree
    Turret three is a piercing turret dealing more damage and piercing enemy armor.
    TowerTwo
    Turret two is an area damage turret.
    ValueBar
    A value bar class that displays values written in text form.
    Video  
    WelcomeVideo
    Video that plays before the game starts
    WelcomeWorld
    Title screen of the game
